headline: From AI Darlings To Dow Dinosaurs: Investors Flee Software For Old-Economy Stocks
summary: Software stocks are sliding as AI disruption fears grow, but investors aren't panicking. Goldman Sachs shows capital rotating toward AI-insulated, real-economy sectors.

headline: Deere Expands U.S. Manufacturing To Support Equipment Reliability And Earnings Quality
summary: Deere (NYSE:DE) is expanding its U.S. manufacturing footprint with new facilities in Indiana and North Carolina. The company plans a distribution center in Indiana and a new excavator factory in North Carolina, shifting certain excavator production from Japan to the U.S. The projects are expected to generate hundreds of jobs and increase domestic supply chain capacity.
